Avoid the lass

If you didn’t catch a Flyer yet, catch a Spearow/Pidgey now in the grass below the lass (Bubble to weaken)
- If you come across a Nidoran and don't have a Rattata either, you can catch it (can learn Cut and Strength)

Grab the hidden Persim Berry to the left of the poke center
Optional: Buy Magikarp (useful as switch fodder) and heal in the center (to preserve potions)
Enter Mt. Moon

Mt. Moon menu:
  - Register the TM case
  - Give the Persim Berry to Squirtle
  - Use a Repel

Grab the Rare Candy below the Bug Catcher and the escape rope  
Get TM Thief and hidden Ether (down the ladder near youngster Josh)  
Fight Hiker Marcos

:::::::trainer[Hiker Marcos]
  - Bubble x3
:::::::

Get the Revive.  
Catch Zubat on B2F.  
Tackle if Level 8 or 9, Water Gun if level 10 or 11. Always Bubble in Torrent.  
Repel after you caught it.  
If you catch a Lvl 10 Paras, you can use it to repel trick for Zubat.  
Before the mandatory Rocket, switch Zubat to the front, switch setting to shift.
:::if{source="Zubat" condition="startingLevel=8"}
  Teach Zubat Thief.
:::

Note: Whenever Wartortle faints an opponent Pokemon, all strats below assume that you then switch back to Zubat immediately.

:::::::trainer[Rocket Grunt]
  :::::pokemon[Rattata]
	- Switch to Wartortle: WG x2
	::damage[Rattata's Hyper Fang]{source="Squirtle" offensive=false movePower=80 level=16 evolution=1 opponentLevel=13 opponentStat=19 special=false stab=true}
	::damage[Rattata's Quick Attack]{source="Squirtle" offensive=false movePower=40 level=16 evolution=1 opponentLevel=13 opponentStat=19 special=false stab=true}
  :::::
  :::::pokemon[Zubat]
	- Switch to Wartortle: WG x2
        ::damage[Chance to OHKO with WG*]{source="Squirtle" offensive=true movePower=40 level=16 evolution=1 opponentStat=13 healthThreshold=33 special=true stab=true torrent=true}
  :::::
:::::::

:::::::trainer[Super Nerd Miguel]
  :::::pokemon[Grimer]
	- Switch to Wartortle and WG x2-3
  :::::
